@node preq "Finestra della Tavolozza"
@{par}
@{jcenter}@{b}@{fg highlight}Finestra della Tavolozza@{ub}@{fg text}@{par}
@{par}
@{bg fill}@{fg filltext} Modifica tavolozza di ''               | ]@{fg text}@{bg background}@{par}
                 Tavolozza               @{par}
 +----------------------------------------+@{par}
 |                 @{bg shadow}                 @{bg background}|@{par}
 |@{bg shine}                 @{bg background}@{bg fill}                 @{bg background}|@{par}
 +----------------------------------------+@{par}
 [   Copia   ] [    Scambia   ] [  Sfuma  ]@{par}
 [      Ripristina     ][      Disfa      ]@{par}
        ________________________     @{par}
 Rosso [__________@{bg text}__@{bg background}____________] 123@{par}
 Verde [__________@{bg text}__@{bg background}____________] 123@{par}
 Blu   [__________@{bg text}__@{bg background}____________] 123@{par}
@{par}
 [   Ok   ]                     [ Annulla ]@{par}
@{par}
Quando usi la tastiera nella finestra di modifica della tavolozza:@{par}
Per copiare, scambiare o sfumare devi selezionare il primo colore, premere il 
tasto corrispondente all'operazione che vuoi effettuare, selezionare il 
secondo colore usando la tastiera e infine premere di nuovo il tasto 
corrispondente all'operazione che vuoi effettuare.@{par}
@{par}
Menu@{par}
@{par}
·Carica tavolozza@{par}
·Salva tavolozza@{par}
    Queste due voci di menu caricheranno o salveranno la tavolozza nel 
formato colormap IFF ILBM (CMAP) che č compatibile con la maggior parte dei 
programmi di disegno pittorico. Questo significa anche che puoi caricare la 
tavolozza dalla maggior parte delle immagini ILBM.@{par}
·------------@{par}
·Ok@{par}
·Annulla@{par}
@{par}
@endnode

@node history "History"
@smartwrap
@{par}
@{jcenter}@{b}@{fg highlight}History@{ub}@{fg text}@{par}
@{jleft}@{par}
@{b}Ver.Rev (M/D/Y)@{ub}@{par}
· Info@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.39 (1/30/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Update to Spanish and Swedish catalogs.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.39 (12/28/97)@{ub}@{par}
· True color backdrops now work on true color screens. (requires V43
picture.datatype)@{par}
· German catalogs have been updated upto version 4.35, thanks to Andreas
Timmermann@{par}
· Fixed low memory error in LayerHook code.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.38 (12/21/97)@{ub}@{par}
· ModePro's public screens wouldn't close if they had a backdrop.@{par}
· Backdrops are now loaded on ModePro's process.@{par}
· Screens that were not promoted didn't close.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.37 (12/18/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed bug that happened when the OpenScreen patch couldn't allocate memory,
which caused all successive calls to OpenScreen and CloseScreen to be stopped.
@{par}
· New Turkish catalog!@{par}
· Added backdrop support Needs WB3+, (No TrueColor support *YET*!)@{par}
  + Backdrop suport requires WB3+@{par}
  + Uses code from the LayerHook archive@{par}
  + If V43 Picture datatype is loaded, it will load 24bit pictures, @{par}
    however, on true color screens the picture is still dithered.@{par}
  + Loading datatypes needs to be done on a seperate task, currently @{par}
    there is a delay between when the screen opens and when the program @{par}
    opens it's window</li>@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.36 (11/8/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Palette requester now has menus to Load and Save the palette.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.35 (10/12/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Entries that are non-editable are highlighted on WB3+@{par}
The following were added in version 4.34(++), that were only available from my
website. @{par}
· Kludge around centering Picasso96 screens, P96 overscan limits are not
defined.  Now ModePro will not center screens when the overscan settings don't
make sense.   @{par}
· Spanish catalogs, Thanks to Dámaso D. Estévez!@{par}
· Minor change in the way screen hotkeys are delt with internally.@{par}
· More therapy for centering code.  Uses intuition/QueryOverscan() to get
dimensions now.@{par}
  @{par}
@{b}4.34 (8/30/97)@{ub}@{par}
· While ModeProPrefs opens it's windows, the "Ask Unknown ..." options are
temporarily disabled, as soon as the prefs window is opened the settings are
restored.  This is to prevent a deadlock from occuring in case ModeProPrefs
has to open it's own screen, or opens on a non-existing public screen.@{par}
· ModePro's exit code didn't check to see if the CloseWorkbench() patch was
safe to remove. @{par}
· Tweaked the screen centering code.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.33 (7/20/97)@{ub}@{par}
· For WB3.x Users, ModePro now uses the Palette Preference settings for "4
Color" screens for the Default 3-D Look.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.32 (7/20/97)@{ub}@{par}
· ModePro exit code added check to see if anyone is still inside the patch
code.@{par}
· ModeProPrefs could quit before ModePro returned all the messages MPPrefs
sent.  This could cause random crashes when ModePro finally did return the
messages.  Most notably when you selected the old Quit menu item (Now "Quit
ModePro").@{par}
· Crash after the @{"Unknown Screen Requester" link menus} is hopefully gone. @{par}
· Also if ModeProPrefs can't be started after answering the Unknown Screen
Requester, ModePro will time out, and not promote the screen. @{par}
· Changed Hide menu item to "Quit" and "Quit" menu item to "Quit ModePro", to
be more consistent with system preferences.@{par}
· Default HotKey changed from "lcommand p" to "lamiga p", which is the
samething.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.31 (6/15/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Added @{"Sort List" link menus} option to Edit Menu.@{par}
· Reworked the way screen titles are handled when an entry has the Make Public
option selected.  See @{"Public Control Gadgets" link pubcont}. @{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.30 (6/14/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Added Unknown Public Screen option, similar to Unknown screen option.@{par}
  See @{" Unknown Screen Gadgets" link unknownscreengads} and the @{"Ask about unknown Public Screens" link menus} menu
item.  @{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.29 (6/4/97)@{ub}@{par}
· New entries created when an unknown screen is opened will be saved to the
prefs file if you click on "Use" or "Never Again"@{par}
· Fixed in error were MPPrefs didn't use localized strings for a few gadgets@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.28 (5/26/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Reworked the way ModePro deals with unknown screens. See 
@{" Unknown Screen Gadgets" link unknownscreengads} and the @{"Ask about unknown screens" link menus} menu item.  @{par}
· Added Blank Border and Behind @{"options" link options}.@{par}
· Added Default option to @{"3D Look" link 3dlook}.@{par}
· Added Screen Modes to the "Copy to" @{"menu" link menus} items.@{par}
· Fixed bug in "Copy to" menu, when to entry was copied, MPPrefs would
activate the wrong list if you copied to the Screen Names or Program Names
lists.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.26 (5/18/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Finally fixed a major complaint from translators, now ModeProPrefs will
determine the key for a gadget just from the gadget's name, the seperate
entries in ModeProPrefs.cd for the key and shifted key are no longer needed.@{par}
· ModeProPrefs finally sports a resizeable GUI.@{par}
· More to come soon!@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.25 (4/30/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Added Wildcard support for the ScreenMode list.  See 
@{" Promotion List Gadgets" link list} for more info.@{par}
· Fixed Enforcer hit when opening the screen mode requester by clicking on the
"Select Screen Mode..." gadget.  Is really a bug in "asl.library"@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.24 (4/20/97)@{ub}@{par}
· In ModeProPrefs; Removed Promotion options "None" and "Monitor Type" when
the Public Screens list is active since those options don't work.  @{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.23 (4/19/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed bug in MPPrefs where it's window was closed before MPPrefs was done
with it, this bug was introduced in v4.19 with the new GUI code.@{par}
· Fixed bug introduced in 4.17, if you had no entry for the Workbench screen,
and you closed and reopened WB (using ScreenMode for ex.) ModePro would not
open anymore screens or allow MPPrefs to@{par}
open. (Technically, I didn't released a semaphore when I should have)@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.22 (4/16/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed ancient bug where using the Palette option caused the Center options
not to work on WB3+.  @{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.21 (4/13/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Fix bug that was introduced around v4.19, where selecting a promotion list
that was empty would cause the Promotion List Cycle Gadget to not work.@{par}
· Public Screens now have there own list. @{par}
· Added @{b}Copy To@{ub} options,to @{b}Edit@{ub} menu.  See @{"Menus" link menus}  @{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.20 (4/11/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Added the ability to create Public Screen that are opened and closed as
needed.  See @{"Creating a Public Screen Entry" link createpubscreens}.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.19 (4/7/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed bug where using -1 as a value for one of the 3D Look Pens, causing
part of the Pen list to be ignored.@{par}
· Fixed long standing bug which sometimes caused MPPrefs to place it's window
too high if it opened it's own screen.@{par}
· Main GUI and Palette GUI now use same gadget layout code.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.18 (1/25/97)@{ub}@{par}
· Removed some debuging code the was printed to the serial port when using the
@{i}Share Pens & Exclude@{ui} options.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.17 (12/14/96)@{ub}@{par}
· ModePro will take options from it's icon if none are specified on the
command line (Like MPPrefs).@{par}
· Most of ModePro's command line options and tooltypes have been moved to
ModeProPrefs and changed.@{par}
  + All the Catch_ options have been replaced with the @{par}
    "ASK_UNKNOWN" option.@{par}
  + Since "NEWLOOKMENUS", "ENABLE_PROMOTION" "ASK_UNKONWN" @{par}
    "CENTER_xxxx" and "DEBUG" are options of MPPrefs, these@{par}
    options can be changed from the shell or icon without @{par}
    opening the ModeProPrefs window by specifing the "USE" @{par}
    option. @{par}
· MPPrefs menus have been revamped.  The "Catch" menu has been replaced with
the "Settings" menu:@{par}
  + "Enable Screen Promotion" (moved from the Projects menu)@{par}
  + "Enable NewLook Menus"    (moved from the Projects menu)@{par}
  + "Ask about unknown screens" (replaces the CATCH stuff)@{par}
  + "Center unknown screens".  See @{"Menus" link menus} for more info.@{par}
· MPPrefs will now save the options in the Settings menu.@{par}
· New translations.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.16 (10/29/96)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed big bug in the Screen Mode list:@{par}
  + If you didn't choose one of the "(monitor):All" screen modes,@{par}
    MPPrefs always set the screen mode to "Old:NTSC:Low Res" or @{par}
    "Old:PAL:Low Res".@{par}
  + Fix memory leak which was the cause of the above bug, it @{par}
    occured evey time you clicked on "Select" with the Screen Modes@{par}
    list active, every screen mode item in the select list was @{par}
    allocated twice, and only one item was freed.  On top of that@{par}
    the duplicate item that was used was not initiallized completely.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.15 (10/11/96)@{ub}@{par}
· ModePro can be disabled from the commodities Exchange program now.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.14 (9/22/96)@{ub}@{par}
· Bug fix in screenmode promotion.  Using "(Monitor):All" would promote
everything, instead of just promoting that monitor. @{par}
· Attempt to fix glitch where the palette editor may have cut off the first
digits(s) on the Red: Green: & Blue: sliders. @{par}
· Confirmed, the @{b}"CED"@{ub} bug was fixed in 4.13.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.13 (7/25/96)@{ub}@{par}
· Slight change in open window patch in an attempt to fix the {b}"CED"{ub}
bug.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.12 (6/13/96)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed Mungwall hit that occured when screens that use any of the "Font",
"Public Screen", "Hot Key" or "Force Planar" options were closed on systems
running WB3+.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.11 (4/20/96)@{ub}@{par}
· ModePro's command line option CenterAllHoriz and CenterAllVert turned the
option off, instead of turning it on like it should have, fixed.@{par}
· ModePro no longer complains if it can't find the preference settings in ENV:
or ENVARC: at startup.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}(3/30/96)@{ub}@{par}
· 2 years old.  *<|8·)@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.10 (4/8/96)@{ub}@{par}
· Bugfix in ModePro's command line.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.9 (4/6/96)@{ub}@{par}
· Bugfix in palette requester which occured when the bits per blue and green
where not the same.@{par}
· Enhanced BestModeID call. (V39)@{par}
· Little GUI work.  Now remebers where the prefs window was at last, and which
node was being edited.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.8@{ub} beta version@{par}
· Promote Monitor Type now uses the BestModeID function when running on WB3+
systems.  This should give better results when promoting to graphics cards.  @{par}
· Keyboard equivalents for gadgets.@{par}
· Force Planar display option.@{par}
· Fixed error in determining where a screen should be centered to.@{par}
· If MPPrefs has to open a screen for itself to open on, it now uses either
the default system font or the user specified font for the screen instead of
Topaz 8.@{par}
· ModePro has new command line and tooltype options to center all screens that
it does not promote.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.6@{ub} beta version@{par}
· Palette Promotion added.@{par}
· Pressing a screen hotkey will activate a window on that screen.@{par}
· Screen Promotion will can promote all the screenmodes of a particular
monitor. @{par}
· Starting ModeProPrefs from the cli or via the PrefsCommand option of ModePro
with no parameters on the command line will cause the prefs editor to use the
icon tooltypes as options.@{par}
· Setting the Width & Height gadgets to 0 will cause a promoted screen to open
in the dimesions the application specifies.@{par}
· The Center screen option has been expanded to allow horizontal only,
verticle only or centering on both directions.@{par}
· Replaced the Pen Name display and Font display gadgets with my own
functions, which look better@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.5 (11//95)@{ub} debug version.@{par}
· This version of ModePro has a Debug option.@{par}
· Fixed a bug in the Locale support,  basically wasn't allocating the
appropriate amount of ram for the word "New" in the promotion list.  Was
allocating enough for a 9 letter word, which was fine for "New", but not fine
if the translation of "New" was longer than nine letters.@{par}
· Added promotion by ScreenMode.  Easy to implement in the patch, but a pain
in the ass to implement in the prefs editor.@{par}
· Added the Select button to allow you to choose from a list of names or
screenmodes for an entry in the promotion list.  @{par}
· There was a major hole when promoting Workbench.  If the Workbench screen
was closed, and not reopened(an option in many paint programs to save ram),
ModePro would have problems: If a HotKey was assigned to the Workbench screen
and the HotKey was pressed, if the hotkey to bring up the Preferences program
was pressed, and probably some other things as well.@{par}
· Minor interface changes:@{par}
    Changed order of the @{"Promotion List Cycle Gadget" link list} to reflect the priority
of the lists.@{par}
    Wrote my own code to display the number of colors for the 
@{"Color Slider Gadget" link method}.  The original GadTools code was totally unsatisfactory,
esp on WB2.X.@{par}
@{b}4.1 (9/18/95)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed a bug with the OpenWindow patches, which interfered with programs that
used the original OpenWindow() function and used the extended ExtNewWindow
structure.  (Most noticeable in Arq)@{par}
· Allows limited promotion of the Workbench screen.  see @{"Promoting Workbench" link workbench}.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}4.0 (9/5/95)@{ub}@{par}
· Program now comes in two sections, a daemon and a Prefs editor.@{par}
· Cleaned up the 3D Pen list (V39 only)                   @{par}
@{par}
@{b}3.9@{ub}@{par}
· Beta Ver. limited distribution.@{par}
· Screen Hotkeys@{par}
@{par}
@{b}3.6 (7/25/95)@{ub}@{par}
· Beta Ver. not distributed@{par}
· Locale support.@{par}
· Fixed some enforcer read hits. 3 happened when the promotion list is empty
and 2 would happen if no font was selected with the Font option set to
Specify.@{par}
· Fixed glitch where the Depth gadgets where refreshed twice, in a row.  Which
would sometimes cause 2 of the above enforcer hits@{par}
· Fixed the labels in the Overscan gadget, Extreme and Maximum were in the
wrong order.@{par}
· Changed default value of CX_POPUP to YES to be more consistent with the rest
of the system commodities.@{par}
· Now uses ReadArgs() to parse CLI parameters.  @{par}
· Screen to front HotKeys.@{par}
· Cleanup of code for Loading & Saving Prefs.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}3.5 (6/8/95)@{ub}@{par}
· Squashed more bugs. @{par}
· Overhaul of interface code.@{par}
· Added ability to set the interface font. @{"More info" link tooltypes}@{par}
· Support for WB3+ pen sharing.@{par}
· Added ability to set screen depth.@{par}
· Now supports _all_ AmigaDos wild cards. @{"More info" link list}@{par}
· Now frees memory, if allocated, for the File, Font and ScreenMode requester
when ModePro's window is closed, previously the memory was not freed until
ModePro was quit.@{par}
@{par}
@(b)3.2 (4/15/95)@(ub)
· Fixed bug in file saver where info relating to the Font was saved even when
it should not have been(Font modes 'Program' & 'System') this had a side
effect of messing up the Public options if the Font mode was 'Program' or
'System'.@{par}
@(b)3.1 (4/02/95)
· Fixed minor glitch with the Public Name string gadget.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}(3/30/95)@{ub}@{par}
· ModePro is 1 year old :)@{par}
@{par}
@{b}3.0 (3/21/95)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed a major bug(from v2.5) with the Specify font option, which would cause
the font to change on the promoted screens if another promoted screen was
opened with Specify font option and the two fonts were different.@{par}
· Added another system patch to CloseScreen(), this was required to fix the
font bug, and for the new public screen management.              @{par}
· New Font sensitive interface which also required some reworking of the
interface:@{par}
    "HighlightText:" in the pen list is now "High Text:"@{par}
    "Use Screen Mode Requester" is now "Use Screen Requester"@{par}
· MP will again try to promote LikeWorkbench screens.@{par}
· If MP fails at promoting a screen, MP will make a second attempt to open the
screen without promotion.@{par}
· MP will *not* promote the Workbench screen.@{par}
· Most screens can now be made public.  This was more work than I thought it
would be :^)  @{par}
    See @{"Public Options" link pubcont}.@{par}
· When the 'Catch' menus are enabled, newly caught items are added to the top
of the list.(2.8 added to the bottom).  This was done to make things cleaner
and to get rid of some redundant code.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}2.8 (2/20/95)@{ub}@{par}
· Fixed a few minor discrepancies.@{par}
· ModePro no longer promotes screens that use the @{"LikeWorkbench" link likewb} option.@{par}
· Now when a program is run for the shell of cli, the actual program's name
and not "Shell Process" is added added to the Program List if the "Catch
Programs Name" menu is selected.@{par}
· Previously, when a program opened a nameless screen, the screen wouldn't
match with the "#?" wildcard, now it will.@{par}
· Added "<No Name>" keyword for the screen promotion list. See @{"Promotion List" link list}.
@{par}
· The patch has been updated to use less stack. (about 200 bytes less)@{par}
· Fixed a serious bug with the file & font requesters, caused by opening and
closing the requester, then closing and reopening ModePro's window, and then
reopening the requester.@{par}
· ModePro can no longer be forced to quit if another program has patched over
the same library functions ModePro has. This is for your safety :^).@{par}
· When the 'Catch' menus are enabled, newly caught items are now added to the
bottom of the list. This was done to simply window updates.@{par}
· The pen 'Highlight Text' has the space removed because under 2.X the 'H' was
being truncated.@{par}
· Screen mode requesters now list all modes available under 2.X.@{par}
· Basic mop-up of bugs introduced in v2.6 @{par}
@{par}
@{b}2.6 (12/14/94)@{ub}@{par}
· The stack size specified in the v2.5 icon's information was to small, this
caused ModePro to crash when the window was opened.@{par}
· Options not available in WB2.X will be ghosted when run under WB2.x.@{par}
· Fixed the preference file loader, if a file was saved under WB 2.X would not
load the font information correctly under 3.X and vise-versa.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}2.5 (11/26/94)@{ub}@{par}
    Added the ability to:@{par}
· Specify the font,@{par}
· Have screens Interleaved(V39+ only)@{par}
· And have screens centered when they open.@{par}
· Under V39+ ModePro can force windows to open so that there menus use the new
look(black on white), only works on GadTools menus.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}2.3 (10/17/94)@{ub}@{par}
· Bug fix. The string gadget below the list was always displaying the first
item in the list,  but it happened on WB2.04 and probably WB2.1, and not WB3.1
@{par}
@{par}
@{b}2.2 (10/08/94)@{ub}@{par}
· Did something, but I forgot:)@{par}
@{par}
@{b}2.1 (8/03/94)@{ub}@{par}
· Bug fix: Forgot to free ASL file requester memory when ModePro was quit.@{par}
· More code cleaning.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}2.0 (7/07/94)@{ub}@{par}
· New features: user selectable pens for 3-d look commodity hotkey support
added.(finally)@{par}
· Bug fix: File requester now works correctly. (forgot to add a / between the
path and the filename when required)@{par}
@{par}
@{b}1.5 (6/04/94)@{ub}@{par}
· Bug fix: Stupidity error. I forgot to free memory when an entry was removed
or when the program was ended.@{par}
· New features: AmigaDos wildcards can now be used.@{par}
· Priority slider.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}1.3 (5/21/94)@{ub}@{par}
· Bug fix: ModePro wouldn't Unlock the pubscreen that its window was on if
another program opened a screen while ModePro's window was open.@{par}
· Minor menu work@{par}
@{par}
@{b}1.2 (5/19/94)@{ub}@{par}
· Tried to make code WB2.1 compatible.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}1.1 (4/18/94)@{ub}@{par}
· ModePro is now a commodity.@{par}
· Minor code cleaning.@{par}
· Spelling correction.@{par}
@{par}
@{b}1.0 (3/30/94)@{ub}@{par}
· Initial Release@{par}
@{par}
@endnode

@node future "Il futuro di ModePro"
@{par}
@{jcenter}@{b}@{fg highlight}Cose da fare:@{ub}@{fg text}@{par}
@{jleft}@{par}
@{par}
Vorrei avere qualche opinione sull'unificazione in una unica lista delle tre liste di promozione.
@{par}
  A FAVORE: una voce puň avere qualsiasi prioritŕ che vuoi, invece di avere 
le prioritŕ della lista dei nomi schermo maggiori di quelle della lista dei 
nomi programmi.@{par}
  CONTRO: renderŕ la lista meno maneggevole, avendo una sola grande lista al 
posto di tre piccole.  @{par}
@{par}
Ho bisogno di capire perchč questa guida non funziona sul WB2.X!@{par}
@{par}
@endnode

